added.title: Them Jaws
added.description: The Titans' day at the beach is interrupted by something vicious in the ocean.

added.title: Pool Shark
added.description: The Titans encourage King Shark to start playing pool again but he must first learn how to trust his gut.

added.title: Shark Tank
added.description: King Shark wears a tank top and teaches the Titans all about the "tank life."

added.title: Lake Side Story
added.description: While at the lake, Robin falls in love with a female fish and must choose between her and the Titans.

added.title: Megalodon Jackson
added.description: The Titans face-off against a giant shark but soon discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: Original Idea
added.description: After Trigon proclaims the entire bookstore is his domain, Nana informs him that he has no control in the public domain.

added.title: Attention to Detail
added.description: The Titans retreat to an underground bunker after a distress signal, where they enjoy footage from their past adventures, only to notice something isn't right.

added.title: The Ranch
added.description: The Titans must help the crew of Teen Titans Go! move to their new offices.

added.title: TV Knight 9
added.description: Batman and Gordon fight with Alfred over what to watch on TV.

added.title: Four Hundred
added.description: After Teen Titans Go! wins the award for being DC's longest running animated series, a jealous Superman banishes the Titans to world of stop-motion in order to get their show cancelled.

added.title: Hey Pizza!
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg try their best to slow the pizza delivery boy so they can get free pizza.

added.title: Gorilla
added.description: Beast Boy takes over as Alpha male of the Titans when he is in Gorilla-mode and Robin has to figure out how to get back on top.

added.title: Girls' Night Out
added.description: When the guys plan a guys night out, Starfire drags Raven out on a wild adventure of their own.

added.title: You're Fired
added.description: Beast Boy gets fired from the team and the Wonder Twins take his place.

added.title: Super Robin
added.description: Robin's wish comes true and he finally gets superpowers - but at what cost?

added.title: Tower Power
added.description: Cyborg plugs into the control panel of the Titans' tower and drives the others crazy.

added.title: Parasite
added.description: Starfire's new pet is a horribly dangerous parasite, but Robin is the only one who is suspicious of the beast.

added.title: Starliar
added.description: Beast Boy teaches Starfire how to lie and it backfires as her lies get more and more outrageous.

added.title: Staff Meeting
added.description: When the gang breaks Robin's beloved staff, Robin is forced to find a replacement.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: The Check
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais are delighted when Grandpa Louie gives them a check for $5000. They immediately start fantasizing over what to spend it on. But when Mom and Dad say they're going to spend the money on paying bills instead, it's a race to the bank to see who can cash the check first.

added.title: The Pest
added.description: When they find Anais training herself for a brutal showdown, Gumball and Darwin realize their sister is being pestered at school by an annoying kid, Billy. They try to teach her how to resolve the problem peacefully but Billy has other ideas.

added.title: The Sale
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are devastated to learn that Mr. Robinson, their favorite person in the world, is selling his house and leaving town. When they realize that making some final happy memories with Mr. Robinson is not enough for them, they decide to stop him leaving by sabotaging the sale.

added.title: The Gift
added.description: After they receive an extravagant invitation to Masami's birthday party, Gumball and Darwin are anxious to find just the right gift for her. However, they're not the only ones: it turns out every kid in Elmore is competing to get Masami the perfect present.

added.title: The Parking
added.description: When the Wattersons arrive at the mall for a day of shopping, they struggle to find a space in the parking lot. They search for a space everywhere using all their intelligence, cunning and trickery but as the day goes on, the desperate hunt for a space becomes more important than the trip to the mall itself.

added.title: The Routine
added.description: Mom and the kids depart for their hard day's work, leaving a seemingly lazy Dad half-asleep on the sofa. Mom has given him one very simple job: buy mayonnaise. However, Dad manages to turn this mundane task into an epic quest, showing that his daily routine isn't as inactive as his family imagine.

added.title: The Upgrade
added.description: Gumball and Darwin see an advert for the latest, cutting-edge Bobert operating system and excitedly talk Bobert into downloading it. At first it seems like a massive improvement, but the many flaws in the new operating system become increasingly apparent.

added.title: The Comic
added.description: Gumball is the star of his own comic, but struggles to match up to his heroic alter-ego.

added.title: The Romantic
added.description: After Gumball convinces himself that Penny doesn't love him as much as she used to, he decides to put together a romantic quest to remind her of all the good times they've had together. But Gumball's romantic gesture backfires, landing Penny and maybe their relationship in serious peril.

added.title: The Uploads
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to tear themselves away from the internet, but end up falling down the Elmore Stream-hole.

added.title: The Apprentice
added.description: Gumball decides that the best way to prove to Mr. Fitzgerald that he's good enough for Penny is to become his apprentice for the day. The problem is Mr. Fitzgerald has an important interview and Gumball's enthusiastic attempts to help him might actually do more harm than good, both to Mr. Fitzgerald's business and to Gumball's future with Penny.

added.title: The Hug
added.description: When Darwin taunts Gumball about how predictable he is, Gumball tries to prove he can still surprise his buddy. He thinks greeting a kid he barely knows with a hug will do the trick. He's right but doesn't see the awkward social repercussions of the hug coming.

added.title: The Wicked
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to find a single nice quality about their neighbor, Mrs Robinson.

added.title: The Traitor
added.description: When Alan ditches Gumball to do something more fun, Gumball is desperate to track him down and make him pay for his betrayal.

added.title: The Origins
added.description: When Mom and Dad struggle to keep hyperactive, toddler-aged Gumball from trashing the house and exhausting them, they decide to buy him a pet. It works, but there's a problem: every goldfish they get him is short-lived, and inevitably ends up being flushed down the toilet.

added.title: The Chef's Challenge
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves entering a cooking battle for a piece of the cube.

added.title: The Sparkle Solution
added.description: When Craig is having trouble with some math homework, Sparkle Cadet comes to the rescue.

added.title: Better Than You
added.description: The Squashinator challenges Craig to a battle he can't refuse.

added.title: The Dream Team
added.description: Craig and his cousin, Bryson, join forces for an action packed weekend at their grandparents house.

added.title: Fire & Ice
added.description: Kelsey and Stacks write a story for book club, which turns out to be more personal than Kelsey realized.

added.title: Chrono Moss
added.description: Craig and his friends come upon a mysterious Moss Village, which could aid them in their quest for the Heart of the Forest.

added.title: In Search of Lore
added.description: Craig searches for more clues to aid his quest for the Heart of the Forest.

added.title: Opposite Day
added.description: Opposite Day turns out to be the opposite of what nobody didn't think it wouldn't be.

added.title: Adventures in Baby Casino
added.description: Craig goes all in at the Baby Casino.

added.title: Creek Talent Extravaganza
added.description: Hoping to help the Creek Daycare, Craig organizes a talent show.

added.title: Dodgy Decisions
added.description: Friends and rivals are pitted against each other in a dangerous game of dodgeball.

added.title: Hyde & Zeke
added.description: Craig and his friends are challenged to find the greatest hider that Hide and Seek has ever known.

added.title: The Anniversary Box
added.description: Craig is entrusted with a special anniversary gift for his mom, and immediately loses it in the Creek.

added.title: Lost & Found
added.description: Craig and his friends visit the Creek's Lost & Found, hoping to claim a puzzle cube.

added.title: Grandma Smugglers
added.description: Craig helps Raj sneak his grandmother away to the Creek.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: Cat Fingers
added.description: Steven attempts to master the power of shape shifting, but can only shape shift his fingers into tiny cat heads.

added.title: Bubble Buddies
added.description: Steven looks like a hero when he forms a magic crystal bubble around himself to protect a girl he likes from danger, but then panics when he can't figure out how to turn the bubble off!

added.title: Serious Steven
added.description: Steven tries to prove himself to be a worthy Crystal Gem to Garnet while they navigate their way out of an ancient Gem maze.

added.title: Tiger Millionaire
added.description: Steven joins Amethyst in an underground wrestling league.

added.title: Steven's Lion
added.description: Steven makes friends with a magical lion, but can't quite tell why it likes him.

added.title: Arcade Mania
added.description: Steven takes the Crystal Gems to Funland Arcade where Garnet learns the allure of video games.

added.title: Giant Woman
added.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

added.title: So Many Birthdays
added.description: So Many Birthdays: Steven learns that the Crystal Gems are thousands of years old and decides to make up for all the thousands of birthdays they've missed.

added.title: Lars and the Cool Kids
added.description: Steven and Lars get to hang out with the cool kids in town, but their teenage shenanigans get them into magical trouble.

added.title: Onion Trade
added.description: A boy trade between Steven and Onion escalates to epic proportions.

added.title: Steven the Sword Fighter
added.description: Pearl tries to teach Steven the art of sword-fighting using a holographic version of himself.

added.title: Lion 2: The Movie
added.description: Steven and Connie try to ride the Lion to the movie theater but Lion has other ideas.

added.title: Beach Party
added.description: After a battle damages Fish Stew Pizza, Steven throws a cookout at the Temple to mend the relationship between Pizza family and the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Rose's Room
added.description: Steven's desire for some alone time unlocks a new room in the Temple that answers his every wish.

added.title: Coach Steven
added.description: After seeing Gamet and Amethyst fuse together into the powerful Sugilit - Steven becomes determined to get super strong.

added.title: Stakes Part 5: May I Come In?
added.description: Finn, Jake, Marceline, and PB set out to hunt down the Vamps. But who is hunting them?

added.title: Stakes Part 6: Take Her Back
added.description: While Princess Bubblegum searches for a cure for Marceline, Finn & Jake take on one of the Vamps themselves.

added.title: Stakes Part 7: Checkmate
added.description: On the eve of battle, Marceline's archenemy comes to her with a strange proposal.

added.title: Stakes Part 8: The Dark Cloud
added.description: The final confrontation! Who will survive?

added.title: The More You Moe, the Moe You Know
added.description: Moe visits the tree house with a special birthday surprise for BMO. While BMO's mission stands on the brink of disaster, Finn & Jake host a strange guest.

added.title: Summer Showers
added.description: Jake's daughter Viola is up for a role in a play by a hot new director, Lumpy Space Princess.

added.title: Angel Face
added.description: BMO ropes his friends into a live action cowboy role-playing adventure!

added.title: President Porpoise Is Missing
added.description: Finn and Jake must find President Porpoise before Vice President Blowfish takes over! It's chaos under the sea!

added.title: Blank Eyed Girl
added.description: One very spooky night, Finn and Jake come face-to-face with an urban myth.

added.title: Bad Jubies
added.description: There's a catastrophic storm headed for the Grasslands so Finn, LSP and BMO decide to build a bunker for protection, but Jake has plans of his own.

added.title: A King's Ransom
added.description: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

added.title: Scamps
added.description: Finn takes a group of at-risk Candy Kingdom youth on a camping trip they'll never forget.

added.title: Crossover
added.description: Prismo needs Finn and Jake's help to stop a catastrophic event from happening somewhere in the multiverse.

added.title: Hall of Egress
added.description: Trapped and alone, Finn must unravel the riddle of the weird cave with no exit.

added.title: Flute Spell
added.description: Jake learns that Finn's been having clandestine meetings with a powerful wizard. But what are they up to?

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: New Bro on Campus
added.description: High School Muscle Man wants to prove he's cooler than the new kid on campus.

added.title: Daddy Issues
added.description: C.J. wants to win a "cut the Cheeser's" card at a mini-golf tournament.

added.title: The End of Muscle Man
added.description: The guys want to help Muscle Man finish his bucket list.

added.title: Lift With Your Back
added.description: Rigby wants to prove to Mordecai that he can earn a paycheck from another job.

added.title: Eileen Flat Screen
added.description: Rigby wants to set up Eileen's flat screen TV for her.

added.title: White Elephant Gift Exchange
added.description: The park guys want revenge on Muscle Man for all his terrible gifts.

added.title: Merry Christmas Mordecai
added.description: Mordecai has to get through a Christmas party with C.J. without messing everything up.

added.title: Sad Sax
added.description: Mordecai wants to get back together with C.J.

added.title: Park Managers' Lunch
added.description: The park guys want to make sure Benson gets back safe from his lunch with Gene.

added.title: Slam Dunk
added.description: Mordecai needs access to the computer so he and Rigby challenge Muscle Man and High Five Ghost to a basketball game for a week's worth of computer time.

added.title: Weekend at Benson's
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally knock out Benson and try to cover it up.

added.title: Eggscellent
added.description: Mordecai wants to win a hat for Rigby.

added.title: The Power
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby find a mysterious keyboard that allows them to do anything they want, including accidently sending Benson to the moon.

added.title: Prank Callers
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try and prank the Master Prank Caller to be the best prank callers. The MPC sends them back to 1982.
